The paper deals with solving random subset sum instances, which are commonly used in cryptography. This suggests that cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the application of the algorithm to decoding random binary linear codes, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The algorithm itself is search tree-based, which suggests that cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of stochastic techniques, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
